The paper describes a data-driven method for classifying patients with vascular mild cognitive impairment (VMCI) into Traditional Chinese Medicine (TCM) syndrome types based on symptom co-occurrence patterns. This involves performing latent tree analysis on a large data set of patient symptoms. The paper is likely to fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE), databases (cs.DB), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) due to the use of data-driven methods and the potential application of the results in clinical practice and research.
